Name: Description
Imp-class: An operating model component that specifies the degree of adherence to management recommendations (Implementation error)

Name: Function call
Imp-class: Objects can be created by calls of the form new('Imp')

Name: Name
Imp-class: The name of the Implementation error object

Name: TACSD
Imp-class: lognormal standard deviation in fraction of TAC taken (uniform distribution)

Name: TACFrac
Imp-class: Mean fraction of TAC taken (uniform distribution) (can be an improper fraction greater than 1)

Name: ESD
Imp-class: lognormal standard deviation in fraction of TAE taken(uniform distribution)

Name: EFrac
Imp-class: Mean fraction of recommended effort taken (uniform distribution)

Name: SizeLimSD
Imp-class: lognormal error in size limit implementation (uniform distribution)

Name: SizeLimFrac
Imp-class: Mean fraction of the size limit (uniform distribution) (can be an improper fraction greater than 1)

Name: DiscMort
Imp-class: Discard mortality rate (uniform distribution) (can be an improper fraction greater than 1)

Name: Source
Imp-class: A reference to a website or article form which parameters were taken to define the operating model
